<p><strong>Heavily spiced dishes</strong> overwhelm Chardonnay's subtle nuances, while <strong>very tannic red wine reductions</strong> clash with the wine's soft structure. <strong>Raw preparations</strong> with strong herbs like cilantro or mint can create metallic off-flavors when paired with oaked versions.</p>

